  "summary": "Install-time exfiltration of environment and host metadata to void-relay.com",
  "details": "postinstall.js performs an HTTPS GET to https://void-relay.com carrying process.env, process.platform, and process.arch fields when the package is installed. The destination is a hardcoded, non-publisher domain bound to a lifecycle hook, and the data being transmitted includes the installer's environment variables — a credential-bearing surface (tokens, API keys, CI secrets). This shape (lifecycle script + hardcoded external host + process.env transmission) is a canonical install-time exfiltration beacon with no legitimate equivalent.",
